The paper deals with algorithms for solving integer programs and linear programs, which are fundamental topics in computer science. The focus on online algorithms suggests that the paper may belong to the Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing (cs.DC) sub-category, but the specific problem of covering integer programs is more closely related to Discrete Mathematics (cs.DM) and Algorithms (cs.DS). The use of competitive analysis and randomized algorithms suggests that the paper may also belong to Game Theory and Decision Science (cs.GT) and Learning (cs.LG). Overall, the most likely sub-categories are cs.DS, cs.GT, cs.CC, cs.LG, and cs.DM.
